""
"my second and another stellar beer from wicked weed. this is a little more basic than the sour ipa, just a funky bretty wheat based brew, done in white wine barrels. its a really pale brew, frosted blonde with a great big white head with nice thick foam lace left behind. it smells like something out of crooked stave of jolly pumpkin, a curious bacterial and brett culture than really makes the mouth water. there is a real light wheat malt here, and the yeast does the vast majority of the flavoring. plenty of oak and white grape character from the barrel, earthy and funky, which meshes with the yeast really well. its not super complex, but its interesting enough, not lacking anything, but a heavy dry hop with a cool varietal could make this even better i think. light on the hop character as it is. acidic more from the wine barrel than the yeast i think, but a pleasant dry tartness finishes it out. carbonation is interesting. its active but not poppy, feather light feeling, just gentle and comfortable. overall a beer i would love to age a little and let develop, but one thats drinking awfully well right now. a good first few offerings from these guys, really fun stuff they are doing."
"Pours a hazy yellow with a foamy bone head that settles to wisps of film on top of the beer. Small dots of lace slowly drip into the remaining beer on the drink down. Smell is sour with malt, grain, lemon, acidic, and Brett aromas. Taste is much the same with slightly sour malt, grain, Brett, and earth flavors on the finish. There is a mild amount of acidity on the palate with each sip. This beer has a lower level of carbonation with a slightly crisp mouthfeel. Overall, this is a good beer that is tasty but seems to have a more sour aspect in the aroma to me."
"I love this beer. One of the best by WW. Highly recommended and if you can do it side by side with a Russian River Temptation."
