"I see this beer developing into a real treasure in another 6-12 months; maybe even longer. All the reviews I have seen show people complaining that it isn’t funky our sour enough for them. Honestly, this tastes just like it should. It is not a wild ale. It is a Saison aged in wine barrles with Brett, and it smells and tastes liek it should. People get so upset when a style isn’t what they think it should be. It is in the ballpark of the style and a wonderful introductory offering from Wicked Weed in terms of bottle options. Search it out with confidence"
